message: "If you use this code, configurations, or artifact pipeline, please cite this repository and the accompanying thesis/paper."
type: software
title: "Reasoning and Grounded Explanation Generation Using Vision-Language Models"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-23"
authors:
  - family-names: "Valijonov"
    given-names: "Komron"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Kamran151199/thesis"
url: "https://github.com/Kamran151199/thesis"
abstract: >-
  Code, experiment configurations, Colab pipeline, final figures, and LaTeX
  sources for a controlled study of resource-constrained vision-language model
  fine-tuning. The study compares answer-only, rationale-generative,
  explanation-aware, BLIP-2 generative, and BLIP-2 contrastive-enhanced
  supervision across document, chart, science, commonsense, and natural-image
  visual question answering settings.
keywords:
  - vision-language models
  - visual question answering
  - explanation-aware learning
  - BLIP-2
  - Qwen2-VL
  - QLoRA
  - reproducibility
